            "coding": [
              {
                "system": "urn:virpat:fhir:doc-type",
                "code": "patient-description"
              }
            ]
          }
        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} is an energetic 8-year-old boy with a round, rosy-cheeked face, currently looking a bit under the weather with red-rimmed nostrils and slightly glassy eyes. He is of average build for his age, dressed in a superhero-themed hoodie and sneakers. Today, his mother brought him into the clinic after he woke up with a runny nose, sneezing, and a sore throat that has been bothering him since yesterday afternoon.\n\n{patientName} attends second grade at a local elementary school, where he is known for being enthusiastic about soccer and drawing comic books with his friends during lunch breaks. He lives with his parents and a younger sister in a suburban home, and he has a pet dog named \"Rocket.\" His diet is typical for his age — he enjoys pasta, sandwiches, and the occasional fruit, but has a strong dislike for vegetables.\n\nOn examination today, {patientName} appears mildly fatigued but is still interactive and talkative. He complains of a stuffy, runny nose with clear discharge, a scratchy throat, mild sneezing, and a low-grade temperature. He denies ear pain, difficulty swallowing solids, or significant difficulty breathing. His mother reports he had a similar episode last winter that resolved on its own within a week.\n\nAt home, {patientName} enjoys playing video games on weekends, riding his bicycle in the neighborhood, and attending soccer practice twice a week. He sleeps approximately 9–10 hours a night and generally has a healthy level of physical activity. His classmates have also been experiencing similar cold-like symptoms over the past week, suggesting a likely school-based viral spread.\n\n{patientName}'s mother is attentive and health-conscious, asking specifically about symptom relief options and whether antibiotics are needed. She confirms he has not traveled recently, has no known sick contacts outside school, and has been up to date on all recommended childhood vaccinations."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "fullUrl": "urn:uuid:dd1f2bca-1f55-4a19-99aa-5970f871c104",
      "resource": {
