        ],
        "subject": {
          "reference": "urn:uuid:11111111-1111-4111-8111-111111111111"
        },
        "payload": [
          {
            "contentString": "{patientName} has no significant chronic medical conditions. He was born at full term via vaginal delivery without complications and met all developmental milestones appropriately. He has a prior history of one episode of acute otitis media at age 5, which was treated with a short course of amoxicillin. He experienced a similar mild upper respiratory tract infection last winter that resolved without medical intervention within one week.\n\n{patientName} has no history of asthma, allergic rhinitis, or recurrent respiratory infections. He has never been hospitalized and has not undergone any surgical procedures. His immunization record is up to date, including annual influenza vaccination. There is no history of exposure to tobacco smoke at home. His mother reports that several of his classmates have had cold-like symptoms in the past week, consistent with a viral cluster in his school environment."
          }
        ]
      }
